        Prepares the given execution context and returns a new instance of a specific service implementation.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The service interface the caller expects
        Parameters:
        type - The type of the service (should match the expected service interface)
        executionContext - The execution context (will be updated and prepared accordingly)
        requiredUser - The id of the user which has to match with the currently authenticated user id
        serviceId - Null or the id of the vendor which can be used to force a specific vendor implementation.
